==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: seasonal affective disorder
<hw>seasonal affective disorder</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
form of mild depression that occurs in winters, associated with
reduction in the amount of sunlight. It is characterized by
oversleeping, irritability, and sometimes overeating. It can be treated
by light therapy and usually disappears with the arrival of
spring.</def> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seasoner</ent>⟦br⟧
